Stpeps to setup Jenkins Master Slave Archicture

=== Create a master node ===
1. Foolow the normal jenkins server installation steps to create the master node

==Creating a Slave node=
1. Create ec2 instance
2. install git
    sudo apt update
    sudo apt install git -y
3. install java
    $ sudo apt update
    $ sudo apt install default-jdk -y

4. create a directory in /home/ubuntu which will act as root directory for the slave machine eg /home/ubuntu/jenkins
note: jenkins is not required to be install in the slave machine

=Configuring the slave nodes on the master node==
1. goto jenkins dashboard -> manager jenins -> Manage nodes and cloud
2. click new node -> enter name -> Select permanent agent
3. enter remote root directory path that we added in the slave node
4. add label -> select launch agent via ssh 
5. give host as "slave vm dns url" by pasting the public dns url of the ec2 machine
6. add credentials (select kind as : ssh username with private key)
7. enter username as ubuntu
8. select private ket as enter drectly and copy the private key contents there
9. select host key strategy as "manually trusted key verification strategy"
10. apply and save